<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1071,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1071,1096]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The following unambiguous apomorphies obtained through equal weighting analysis diagnose 
<taxonomicName box="[151,309,1109,1132]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Ectrepopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,309,1109,1132]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Ectrepopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(ordered according to their consistency indexes). Characters 62, 
<number box="[1034,1120,1108,1132]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="67168.0">67, 168</number>
, and 
<number box="[1179,1221,1108,1132]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="310.0">310</number>
were also found as unambiguous autapomorphies of 
<taxonomicName box="[525,683,1145,1168]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Ectrepopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[525,683,1145,1168]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Ectrepopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the implied weighting analysis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1071,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
- 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[220,478,1179,1204]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
(
<collectingCountry box="[228,266,1179,1204]" name="Switzerland" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Ch</collectingCountry>
. 
<number box="[281,328,1179,1204]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="168.0">168</number>
: 
<number box="[334,349,1179,1204]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
; ci = 
<number box="[419,470,1179,1204]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="0.33">0.33</number>
)
</emphasis>
Foramen in posterior region of metapterygoid that serves as passage for the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">ramus mandibularis</emphasis>
of the 
<emphasis box="[377,497,1217,1240]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">trigeminus</emphasis>
nerve forms an incomplete arch, bordered posteriorly by the hyomandibula (
<figureCitation box="[1353,1422,1215,1239]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[172,1404,1047,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1018,1892]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Ectrepopterus uruguayensis, UFRGS 8578, 37.4 mm SL, male. Lower and upper jaws showing the premaxilla (PMX), maxilla (MAX) and dentary (DEN), and suspensorium showing the foramen in posterior region of metapterygoid (MTP) forming an incomplete arch and bordered posteriorly by the hyomandibula (HYO), left side. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210068/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[1405,1422,1215,1239]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). This foramen is situated entirely within the metapterygoid among characid fishes lacking a supraorbital. The condition found in 
<taxonomicName box="[367,525,1289,1312]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Ectrepopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[367,525,1289,1312]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Ectrepopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is apomorphic, and a reversal, since the foramen opening posteriorly is found in several basal lineages of the 
<taxonomicName box="[499,625,1324,1348]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Characidae</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[647,659,1325,1348]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">e</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[666,680,1325,1348]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">g</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Muller and Troschel 1844" authorityName="Muller and Troschel" authorityYear="1844" box="[700,1103,1324,1348]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[700,781,1325,1348]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Brycon</emphasis>
Müller and Troschel 
<number box="[1044,1103,1324,1348]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="1844.0">1844</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kner 1858" authorityName="Kner" authorityYear="1858" box="[1119,1379,1324,1348]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Iguanodectidae" genus="Bryconops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1119,1239,1325,1348]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Bryconops</emphasis>
Kner 
<number box="[1320,1379,1324,1348]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="1858.0">1858</number>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cope 1872" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1872" box="[151,435,1359,1384]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Iguanodectidae" genus="Iguanodectes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,301,1360,1384]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Iguanodectes</emphasis>
Cope 
<number box="[376,435,1359,1383]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="1872.0">1872</number>
</taxonomicName>
; see 
<bibRefCitation author="Mirande" box="[492,656,1359,1383]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" refString="Mirande, J. M. (2010) Phylogeny of the family Characidae (Teleostei: Characiformes): from characters to taxonomy. Neotropical Ichthyology, 8, 385 - 568." type="journal article" year="2010">
Mirande 
<number box="[595,656,1359,1383]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This condition was found homoplastically in 
<taxonomicName authority="Regan 1908" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1908" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Bryconamericus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scleroparius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Bryconamericus scleroparius</emphasis>
(Regan 
<number box="[341,398,1396,1420]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="1908.0">1908</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
and in 
<taxonomicName authority="Perugia 1891" authorityName="Perugia" authorityYear="1891" box="[490,951,1396,1420]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Pseudocorynopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="doriae">
<emphasis box="[490,792,1396,1420]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Pseudocorynopoma doriae</emphasis>
Perugia 
<number box="[892,951,1396,1420]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="1891.0">1891</number>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1071,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
- 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[219,475,1431,1456]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
(
<collectingCountry box="[227,265,1431,1456]" name="Switzerland" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Ch</collectingCountry>
. 
<number box="[280,330,1431,1456]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="310.0">310</number>
: 
<number box="[335,348,1431,1456]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
; ci = 
<number box="[417,468,1431,1456]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="0.1">0.10</number>
)
</emphasis>
Pectoral-fin rays bearing hooks. Although the presence of hooks in the fin rays is a condition shared by most characid fishes (
<bibRefCitation author="Malabarba" box="[630,990,1468,1492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" refString="Malabarba, L. R. &amp; Weitzman, S. H. (2003) Description of new genus with six new species from southern Brazil, Uruguay and Argentina, with a discussion of a putative characid clade (Teleostei: Characiformes: Characidae). Comunicacoes do Museu de Ciencias e Tecnologia da PUCRS, Serie Zoologia, 16, 67 - 151." type="journal article" year="2003">
Malabarba and Weitzman 
<number box="[930,990,1468,1492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), its presence in the pectoral fin rays is not usual and was found by parsimony as diagnostic for 
<taxonomicName box="[796,953,1505,1528]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Ectrepopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[796,953,1505,1528]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Ectrepopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It was found homoplastic in 
<taxonomicName authority="Gery 1972" authorityName="Gery" authorityYear="1972" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Astyanax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="asuncionensis">
<emphasis box="[1296,1399,1504,1528]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Astyanax</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[151,308,1541,1564]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">asuncionensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gery" box="[316,438,1540,1564]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" refString="Gery, J. (1972) Corrected and supplemented descriptions of certain characoid fishes described by Henry W. Fowler, with revisions of several of their genera. Studies on the Neotropical Fauna, 7, 1 - 35." type="journal article" year="1972">
Géry 
<number box="[380,438,1540,1564]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="1972.0">1972</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Casciotta and Almiron 2004" authorityName="Casciotta and Almiron" authorityYear="2004" box="[451,873,1540,1564]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Astyanax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chico">
<emphasis box="[451,544,1540,1564]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">A. chico</emphasis>
Casciotta and Almirón 
<number box="[814,873,1540,1564]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Perugia 1891" authorityName="Perugia" authorityYear="1891" box="[885,1185,1540,1564]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Astyanax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lineatus">
<emphasis box="[885,902,1540,1564]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[917,1006,1540,1564]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">lineatus</emphasis>
(Perugia 
<number box="[1117,1176,1540,1564]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="1891.0">1891</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Azpelicueta, Casciotta and Almiron 2002" authorityName="Azpelicueta, Casciotta and Almiron" authorityYear="2002" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Astyanax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="troya">
<emphasis box="[1197,1287,1540,1564]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">A. troya</emphasis>
Azpelicueta, Casciotta and Almirón 
<number box="[412,471,1576,1600]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Eigenmann 1893" authorityName="Eigenmann" authorityYear="1893" box="[482,924,1576,1600]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Bario" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="steindachneri">
