; ci = 
<number box="[393,443,1683,1708]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="0.06">0.06</number>
)
</emphasis>
Posterior margin of second infraorbital posteroventrally oblique and second infraorbital ventrally bordering anterior region of third infraorbital (
<figureCitation box="[794,863,1720,1744]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[201,310,1205,1230]" captionTargetBox="[255,1321,199,1157]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[215,1372,155,1184]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Ectrepopterus uruguayensis, UFRGS 8578, 37.4 mm SL, male. Infraorbital series (IO 1 – 6) and antorbital (AOR), left side. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210069/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[848,863,1720,1744]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). This condition is usually associated with a long maxilla, and is found homoplastic in 
<taxonomicName authority="Muller and Troschel 1844" authorityName="Muller and Troschel" authorityYear="1844" box="[572,1088,1756,1780]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Exodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="paradoxus">
<emphasis box="[572,784,1756,1780]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Exodon paradoxus</emphasis>
Müller and Troschel 
<number box="[1029,1088,1756,1780]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="1844.0">1844</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Eigenmann and Norris 1900" authorityName="Eigenmann and Norris" authorityYear="1900" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Hollandichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="multifasciatus">
<emphasis box="[1100,1436,1756,1780]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Hollandichthys multifasciatus</emphasis>
(Eigenmann and Norris 
<number box="[421,481,1792,1816]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="1900.0">1900</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[500,636,1792,1816]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Oligosarcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[500,636,1792,1816]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Oligosarcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., and several genera of the 
<taxonomicName box="[989,1119,1792,1816]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Characinae">Characinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1071,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
- 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[218,457,1827,1852]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
(
<collectingCountry box="[226,264,1827,1852]" name="Switzerland" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Ch</collectingCountry>
. 
<number box="[278,311,1827,1852]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="67.0">67</number>
:0; ci = 
<number box="[399,449,1827,1852]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="0.03">0.03</number>
)
</emphasis>
Fourth infraorbital (
<figureCitation box="[690,758,1828,1852]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[201,310,1205,1230]" captionTargetBox="[255,1321,199,1157]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[215,1372,155,1184]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Ectrepopterus uruguayensis, UFRGS 8578, 37.4 mm SL, male. Infraorbital series (IO 1 – 6) and antorbital (AOR), left side. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210069/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[744,758,1828,1852]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) more developed longitudinally than dorsoventrally (
<emphasis box="[1364,1435,1829,1852]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">versus</emphasis>
longer dorsoventrally than longitudinally). Although apomorphic for 
<taxonomicName box="[971,1128,1865,1888]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Ectrepopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[971,1128,1865,1888]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Ectrepopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this character is broadly distributed among 
<taxonomicName box="[361,491,1900,1924]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Characidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1071,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
